<meta name="assert" content="This test verifies that a position:sticky element aligning with 'auto' margin still honors the sticky positioning.">

<style>
#container{
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: red;
}
.block {
  width: 340282366920938463463374607431768210957px;
}
.child {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  background: green;
  position: sticky;
  margin-left: auto;
  right: 0;
}
</style><div id="container">

<p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>
<style>
  <div class="block">
    <div class="child">
  </div>
